From: Nadia Chambers <nadia.yvette.chambers@ik.me>
Date: Sun, 22 Mar 2026 22:40:36 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 038/174] =?UTF-8?q?PGCL:=20loongarch64=20PAGE=5FMMUSHIFT?=
 =?UTF-8?q?=3D4=20boot=20=E2=80=94=2015/15=20pgcl-test=20+=208/8=20pgcl-st?=
 =?UTF-8?q?ress=20PASS?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

LoongArch page table geometry must use MMUPAGE-sized tables (hardware PTW
via lddir/ldpte expects MMUPAGE granularity). Fix all page table shift and
size calculations: PTRS_PER_PGD/PMD/PTE use MMUPAGE_SIZE >> PTRLOG (2048),
VA_BITS = 47 matching hardware la464. Fix PWCTL width fields in
setup_ptwalker() and index bit widths in tlbex.S software TLB handler.

Fix pte_pfn()/pfn_pte()/pfn_pmd()/pmd_pfn() to use PAGE_SHIFT for
PAGE-granular PFN encoding (pfn_to_page compatibility). Keep PFN_PTE_SHIFT
and _PFN_MASK unchanged to preserve sub-page bits in pte_modify(). Add
pte_advance_pfn override for PAGE-granular PFN advancement.

Fix __set_fixmap() to bypass pfn_pte() with direct __pte() construction
for MMUPAGE-granular MMIO mappings (UART at 0x1FE001E0 needs 16KB-aligned
PTE, not 256KB-aligned). Fix KVM kvm_pfn_pte/kvm_pte_pfn encoding.

Fix HPAGE_SHIFT = 2*MMUPAGE_SHIFT - PTRLOG (= PMD_SHIFT = 25), was
wrongly MMUPAGE_SHIFT + PAGE_SHIFT - PTRLOG (= 29).

Additional PGCL fixes: TLB flush stride (MMUPAGE_SIZE pairs), KFENCE area
size, VMALLOC_END address space, vDSO size/alignment, stack randomization,
mmap color alignment, THREAD_SIZE_ORDER, update_mmu_cache_range stride,
__phys_to_pte_val definition hoisted before set_ptes for PGCL sub-page
encoding.

Config: PAGE_SIZE_16KB + PAGE_MMUSHIFT=4 (MMUPAGE=16KB, PAGE=256KB)
Boot: SMP=4, 15/15 pgcl-test + 8/8 pgcl-stress PASS
Known: blk_validate_limits warning (PAGE_SECTORS with 256KB pages)

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
